      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Joseph Conrad (1857-1924) was a Polish-born British novelist.   Among his important works are <emph render="italic">The Nigger of the 'Narcissus'</emph>  (1897), <emph render="italic">Heart of Darkness</emph> (1899), and  <emph render="italic">Lord Jim</emph> (1900).</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Joseph Conrad Collection</emph> contains seven letters by the British author, the original signed typescript for "Autocracy and War," and a photograph of Conrad at Oswalds, Bishopsbourne, Kent.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
         <p>Letters are arranged chronologically.</p>
      </arrangement>
      
